                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-05-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. McCormick reports that the American commercial agent at Vladivostok has
                    informed him that on request, and in order to better protect the Japanese
                    consular buildings, he has given charge of them to the port admiral, the
                    president of the local Red Cross association; that after removal and storage of
                    the furniture the association has improved the grounds and has renovated the
                    houses for the use of patients and Red Cross nurses. Mr. McCormick informed him
                    that he should have notified the embassy before taking this step, so that
                    consent and approval of the Jananese Government could have been obtained, and
                    added that it is believed that the same would have been cheerfully given.)</p>
            </div>
